
'''* Article: [[Degrowth and Capitalist Power]]: A step towards a theory of change. By Julien Vastenaekels. Degrowth Journal Volume 2 (2024) 00045'''

URL = https://bnarchives.yorku.ca/822/2/20240200_vastenaekels_degrowth_and_capitalist_power.pdf

"''This article explores the relationship between degrowth and the theory of [[Capital as Power]] (CasP), aiming to understand how socio-ecological transformations can unfold against capitalist power dynamics''. While degrowth scholars have largely overlooked this perspective on capital, CasP argues that capitalism is primarily a mode of power, with capitalisation quantifying power – the confidence in in – the ability to shape society against opposition. Key CasP concepts are brought into dialogue with degrowth research to identify potential implications and offer a step towards a theory of change for degrowth."

